#. type: Title =
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using Mail Filters"
msgstr "Using Mail Filters"

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working with Email Filters"
msgstr "Working with Email Filters"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:11
msgid ""
"You can define filters to manage incoming and outgoing email messages, "
"including Calendar-related messages and setting up the Activity Stream "
"filter to manage less important messages. A filter consists of one or more "
"conditions and one or more actions. A condition can be based on a subject, "
"from a specific person, or messages for a particular date. If the message "
"matches the conditions, the specified actions are performed."
msgstr ""
"You can define filters to manage incoming and outgoing email messages, "
"including Calendar-related messages and setting up the Activity Stream "
"filter to manage less important messages. A filter consists of one or more "
"conditions and one or more actions. A condition can be based on a subject, "
"from a specific person, or messages for a particular date. If the message "
"matches the conditions, the specified actions are performed."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:13
msgid "You can create filters to do the following:"
msgstr "You can create filters to do the following:"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Sort incoming messages into folders. For example, all email messages from "
"your supervisor are automatically moved into your Management Directives "
"folder upon receipt."
msgstr ""
"Sort incoming messages into folders. For example, all email messages from "
"your supervisor are automatically moved into your Management Directives "
"folder upon receipt."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Tag messages. For example, email messages from the corporate-events mailing "
"list is marked with the Events tag."
msgstr ""
"Tag messages. For example, email messages from the corporate-events mailing "
"list is marked with the Events tag."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:23
msgid ""
"Forward or discard email. For example, all email messages received from a "
"particular email address is moved to the Trash folder."
msgstr ""
"Forward or discard email. For example, all email messages received from a "
"particular email address is moved to the Trash folder."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:25
msgid "Sort sent messages into specific topic-related folders."
msgstr "Sort sent messages into specific topic-related folders."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:27
msgid "Flag messages for importance."
msgstr "Flag messages for importance."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Filters are applied in the order that they are listed. You can change the "
"order at any time."
msgstr ""
"Filters are applied in the order that they are listed. You can change the "
"order at any time."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:38
msgid ""
"An email message is evaluated by each active filter, unless you specify that "
"a message is treated only by the first filter that it matches. Usually, you "
"do not want other filters applied to a message once there is a match because "
"the message can undergo multiple, perhaps contradictory, actions."
msgstr ""
"An email message is evaluated by each active filter, unless you specify that "
"a message is treated only by the first filter that it matches. Usually, you "
"do not want other filters applied to a message once there is a match because "
"the message can undergo multiple, perhaps contradictory, actions."

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting Up Filter Rules"
msgstr "Setting Up Filter Rules"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:43
msgid ""
"Filter rules consists of one or more conditions and one or more actions. If "
"the message matches the conditions, the specified actions are performed."
msgstr ""
"Filter rules consists of one or more conditions and one or more actions. If "
"the message matches the conditions, the specified actions are performed."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:47
msgid ""
"You can also set Activity Stream rules. Activity Stream rules are set to "
"move less important messages out of your Inbox and into an Activity Stream "
"folder that you can check at your convenience."
msgstr ""
"You can also set Activity Stream rules. Activity Stream rules are set to "
"move less important messages out of your Inbox and into an Activity Stream "
"folder that you can check at your convenience."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a Filter"
msgstr "Creating a Filter"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:53
msgid ""
"You can define filters to manage incoming and outgoing email messages. A "
"filter consists of one or more conditions and one or more actions. If the "
"message matches the conditions, the specified actions are performed."
msgstr ""
"You can define filters to manage incoming and outgoing email messages. A "
"filter consists of one or more conditions and one or more actions. If the "
"message matches the conditions, the specified actions are performed."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:55 usingmailfilters.adoc:137 usingmailfilters.adoc:177
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:412 usingmailfilters.adoc:421
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:435 usingmailfilters.adoc:452
msgid "Go to the *Preferences>Filters* page."
msgstr "Go to the *Preferences>Filters* page."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:57 usingmailfilters.adoc:139
msgid "Click either *Incoming Message Filters* or *Outgoing Message Filters*."
msgstr "Click either *Incoming Message Filters* or *Outgoing Message Filters*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:59 usingmailfilters.adoc:141
msgid "Select *Create Filter*."
msgstr "Select *Create Filter*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:61 usingmailfilters.adoc:143
msgid "In the *Filter Name* text box, enter a unique name for the filter."
msgstr "In the *Filter Name* text box, enter a unique name for the filter."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:64 usingmailfilters.adoc:146
msgid ""
"To make the filter active, check the *Active* box in the upper right corner."
msgstr ""
"To make the filter active, check the *Active* box in the upper right corner."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:66
msgid "Select whether the message must meet any or all the listed conditions."
msgstr "Select whether the message must meet any or all the listed conditions."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:69
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*any* means that if a message meets any one of the conditions, the\n"
"action is performed.\n"
msgstr ""
"*any* means that if a message meets any one of the conditions, the\n"
"action is performed.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*all* means that the message must meet all of the conditions for the\n"
"action to be performed.\n"
msgstr ""
"*all* means that the message must meet all of the conditions for the\n"
"action to be performed.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:75
msgid ""
"From the drop-down menu, select which part of the message to apply to the "
"filter, such as the *Subject* or *From* field."
msgstr ""
"From the drop-down menu, select which part of the message to apply to the "
"filter, such as the *Subject* or *From* field."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:78
msgid ""
"Select how the item must match, such as *contains* or *matches exactly*."
msgstr ""
"Select how the item must match, such as *contains* or *matches exactly*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:81
msgid ""
"Enter or select the information to compare against such as the date, email "
"address, or phrase. Conditions are not case-sensitive."
msgstr ""
"Enter or select the information to compare against such as the date, email "
"address, or phrase. Conditions are not case-sensitive."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:86
msgid ""
"For example, if you selected *Subject* and *contains*, and entered *Staff "
"Meeting*, all messages containing Staff Meeting are filtered. The filter "
"also catches Staff Meetings or Today’s Staff Meeting because you chose "
"*contains* and not *matches exactly*."
msgstr ""
"For example, if you selected *Subject* and *contains*, and entered *Staff "
"Meeting*, all messages containing Staff Meeting are filtered. The filter "
"also catches Staff Meetings or Today’s Staff Meeting because you chose "
"*contains* and not *matches exactly*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:89 usingmailfilters.adoc:154
msgid ""
"(Optional) To add more conditions, click the *+* button and repeat the above "
"steps. The order of the conditions does not matter."
msgstr ""
"(Optional) To add more conditions, click the *+* button and repeat the above "
"steps. The order of the conditions does not matter."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:92
msgid ""
"Under *Perform the following actions*, select an action from the drop-down "
"menu."
msgstr ""
"Under *Perform the following actions*, select an action from the drop-down "
"menu."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:95 usingmailfilters.adoc:160
msgid ""
"Depending on the action that you select, you might need to browse to locate "
"a folder or tag name."
msgstr ""
"Depending on the action that you select, you might need to browse to locate "
"a folder or tag name."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:99
msgid ""
"(Optional) To add more actions, click the *+* button and repeat the above "
"step. The actions are applied in the order in which they are listed."
msgstr ""
"(Optional) To add more actions, click the *+* button and repeat the above "
"step. The actions are applied in the order in which they are listed."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:103 usingmailfilters.adoc:167
msgid ""
"The default is to stop looking for matching filters after the first match. "
"If you want more than one filter to be applied to a message, deselect *Do "
"not process additional filters*."
msgstr ""
"The default is to stop looking for matching filters after the first match. "
"If you want more than one filter to be applied to a message, deselect *Do "
"not process additional filters*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:109
msgid ""
"Usually, you do not want other filters applied to a message once there is a "
"match because the message can undergo multiple, perhaps contradictory, "
"actions."
msgstr ""
"Usually, you do not want other filters applied to a message once there is a "
"match because the message can undergo multiple, perhaps contradictory, "
"actions."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:111
msgid "When you are done creating the filter, click *OK*."
msgstr "When you are done creating the filter, click *OK*."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a Filter from an Email Message"
msgstr "Creating a Filter from an Email Message"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:117
msgid ""
"You can create a filter based on an email message in your Inbox. The filter "
"information is extracted from the message, and you can then modify the "
"conditions and actions."
msgstr ""
"You can create a filter based on an email message in your Inbox. The filter "
"information is extracted from the message, and you can then modify the "
"conditions and actions."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:119
msgid "Right-click an email message and select *Create Filter*."
msgstr "Right-click an email message and select *Create Filter*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:122
msgid ""
"The Add Filter dialog box appears populated with the information from the "
"email message."
msgstr ""
"The Add Filter dialog box appears populated with the information from the "
"email message."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:124
msgid "In the *Filter Name* text box, type a unique name for the filter."
msgstr "In the *Filter Name* text box, type a unique name for the filter."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:127 usingmailfilters.adoc:442
msgid ""
"Change the conditions and actions as necessary using the drop-down menus."
msgstr ""
"Change the conditions and actions as necessary using the drop-down menus."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a Filter for Calendar Invitations"
msgstr "Creating a Filter for Calendar Invitations"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:135
msgid ""
"You can create a filter to organize Calendar invitations you receive. You "
"can filter invitations that you receive and invitations that you send. You "
"can set this filter to act on"
msgstr ""
"You can create a filter to organize Calendar invitations you receive. You "
"can filter invitations that you receive and invitations that you send. You "
"can set this filter to act on"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:148
msgid "In the *Subject* drop-down menu, select *Calendar*."
msgstr "In the *Subject* drop-down menu, select *Calendar*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:151
msgid ""
"Select an *invite is replied/not reply* or *invite is requested/not "
"requested* condition from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Select an *invite is replied/not reply* or *invite is requested/not "
"requested* condition from the drop-down menu."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:157
msgid ""
"Under *Perform the following actions* select an action from the drop-down "
"menu, such as moving an invitation to a specific folder."
msgstr ""
"Under *Perform the following actions* select an action from the drop-down "
"menu, such as moving an invitation to a specific folder."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:163
msgid ""
"(Optional) To add more actions, click the + button and repeat the above "
"step. The actions are applied in the order in which they are listed."
msgstr ""
"(Optional) To add more actions, click the + button and repeat the above "
"step. The actions are applied in the order in which they are listed."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:170
#, no-wrap
msgid "Making a Filter Active or Inactive"
msgstr "Making a Filter Active or Inactive"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:175
msgid ""
"You can turn a filter on or off. If a filter is inactive, it is ignored. "
"Making a filter inactive allows you to keep it for later use rather than "
"deleting it."
msgstr ""
"You can turn a filter on or off. If a filter is inactive, it is ignored. "
"Making a filter inactive allows you to keep it for later use rather than "
"deleting it."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:179 usingmailfilters.adoc:439
msgid "Click *Edit Filter*."
msgstr "Click *Edit Filter*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:182
msgid ""
"Deselect the *Active* box in the upper right corner to turn the filter off."
msgstr ""
"Deselect the *Active* box in the upper right corner to turn the filter off."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filter Conditions"
msgstr "Filter Conditions"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:192
msgid ""
"A filter can contain one or more conditions. For example, if someone sends "
"you email messages from more than one email address and you want to direct "
"all messages from the person into one folder, you can create one filter that "
"has two conditions, one for each email address, and one action to move the "
"email messages to the same folder."
msgstr ""
"A filter can contain one or more conditions. For example, if someone sends "
"you email messages from more than one email address and you want to direct "
"all messages from the person into one folder, you can create one filter that "
"has two conditions, one for each email address, and one action to move the "
"email messages to the same folder."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:198
msgid ""
"The order of the conditions is not important. You can select whether the "
"email message must match all conditions or just meet any one of the listed "
"conditions. You can also use a negative condition. For example, you can "
"filter an email message that does not contain a particular word. Filter "
"conditions are not case-sensitive."
msgstr ""
"The order of the conditions is not important. You can select whether the "
"email message must match all conditions or just meet any one of the listed "
"conditions. You can also use a negative condition. For example, you can "
"filter an email message that does not contain a particular word. Filter "
"conditions are not case-sensitive."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:200
msgid "A filter condition can be based on the following:"
msgstr "A filter condition can be based on the following:"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:202
msgid "Specific email addresses in the From, To, or Cc fields"
msgstr "Specific email addresses in the From, To, or Cc fields"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:204
msgid "Email messages that are under or over a specific size"
msgstr "Email messages that are under or over a specific size"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:206
msgid "Dates"
msgstr "Dates"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:208
msgid "Presence or absence of file attachments"
msgstr "Presence or absence of file attachments"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:210
msgid "Words in the message subject or body"
msgstr "Words in the message subject or body"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:212
msgid "Calendar invitation"
msgstr "Calendar invitation"

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filtering Using _Any_ Versus _All_"
msgstr "Filtering Using _Any_ Versus _All_"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:219
msgid ""
"Conditions within a filter rule can be grouped using *Any* or *All*. The use "
"of these terms is similar to the \"AND\" versus \"OR\" type searches "
"described under the Search feature, with *Any* being OR and *All* being AND."
msgstr ""
"Conditions within a filter rule can be grouped using *Any* or *All*. The use "
"of these terms is similar to the \"AND\" versus \"OR\" type searches "
"described under the Search feature, with *Any* being OR and *All* being AND."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:224
msgid ""
"If you select *Any* when defining conditions for a new filter rule, then a "
"message that meets any one of the conditions is considered a match. However, "
"if you select *All*, every condition specified in that filter rule must "
"apply in order for that message to match the filter."
msgstr ""
"If you select *Any* when defining conditions for a new filter rule, then a "
"message that meets any one of the conditions is considered a match. However, "
"if you select *All*, every condition specified in that filter rule must "
"apply in order for that message to match the filter."

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:225
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filtering Using Contains, Matches, and Is options"
msgstr "Filtering Using Contains, Matches, and Is options"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:230
msgid ""
"Three of the comparison methods for filter conditions are Contains, Matches "
"pattern, and Matches Exactly. These options appear for some items such as "
"the subject line."
msgstr ""
"Three of the comparison methods for filter conditions are Contains, Matches "
"pattern, and Matches Exactly. These options appear for some items such as "
"the subject line."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Contains* means that the specified line must contain, somewhere within\n"
"it, the specified string. For example, specifying that the subject line\n"
"contains \"bananas\" would match both \"Cooking with bananas\" and \"Bananas\n"
"for breakfast\".\n"
msgstr ""
"*Contains* means that the specified line must contain, somewhere within\n"
"it, the specified string. For example, specifying that the subject line\n"
"contains \"bananas\" would match both \"Cooking with bananas\" and \"Bananas\n"
"for breakfast\".\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Matches* pattern means that the specified line must match the\n"
"specified string, which includes wildcards. For example, specifying \"\n"
"bana*\" would match \"banana\" and \"banana tree\" but not \"free bananas\".\n"
msgstr ""
"*Matches* pattern means that the specified line must match the\n"
"specified string, which includes wildcards. For example, specifying \"\n"
"bana*\" would match \"banana\" and \"banana tree\" but not \"free bananas\".\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:244
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Is* means that the specified line must exactly match the specified\n"
"string, with no wildcards or substitutions. For example, specifying\n"
"that the subject line must match \"bananas\" would only match \"bananas\"\n"
"and not \"Banana\", \"My bananas\", or \"Bananas?\"\n"
msgstr ""
"*Is* means that the specified line must exactly match the specified\n"
"string, with no wildcards or substitutions. For example, specifying\n"
"that the subject line must match \"bananas\" would only match \"bananas\"\n"
"and not \"Banana\", \"My bananas\", or \"Bananas?\"\n"

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:245
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filter Conditions and Actions Supported"
msgstr "Filter Conditions and Actions Supported"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:249
msgid ""
"Filter rules are case insensitive, meaning that the rules ignore "
"capitalization."
msgstr ""
"Filter rules are case insensitive, meaning that the rules ignore "
"capitalization."

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:250
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conditions"
msgstr "Conditions"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:253
msgid "Comparison fields include the following:"
msgstr "Comparison fields include the following:"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:256
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*From*. Use this to specify a name in the From: header of an email\n"
"message.\n"
msgstr ""
"*From*. Use this to specify a name in the From: header of an email\n"
"message.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:258
#, no-wrap
msgid "*To*. Same as From, but looks for specified names in the To: header.\n"
msgstr "*To*. Same as From, but looks for specified names in the To: header.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:260
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Cc*. Same as From, but looks in the Cc: header.\n"
msgstr "*Cc*. Same as From, but looks in the Cc: header.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:262
#, no-wrap
msgid "*To or Cc*. Same as From, but looks in both To and Cc header.\n"
msgstr "*To or Cc*. Same as From, but looks in both To and Cc header.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:264
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Subject*. Looks in the message's Subject header.\n"
msgstr "*Subject*. Looks in the message's Subject header.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:269
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Size*. Use this to select email messages that are larger or smaller\n"
"than a specified size. The size of the email includes any file\n"
"attachments. You can use this to discard email messages that are too\n"
"large.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Size*. Use this to select email messages that are larger or smaller\n"
"than a specified size. The size of the email includes any file\n"
"attachments. You can use this to discard email messages that are too\n"
"large.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:272
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Date*. Use this option to specify email messages sent before or after\n"
"a specified date.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Date*. Use this option to specify email messages sent before or after\n"
"a specified date.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:276
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Body*. The options for Body are Contains/Does not contain, and you can\n"
"specify matching words in the body of the email. You cannot filter for\n"
"words in file attachments.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Body*. The options for Body are Contains/Does not contain, and you can\n"
"specify matching words in the body of the email. You cannot filter for\n"
"words in file attachments.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:278
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Read receipt*. Read receipt messages can be filtered.\n"
msgstr "*Read receipt*. Read receipt messages can be filtered.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:281
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Attachment*. Filter for email messages that have, or don't have, file\n"
"attachments.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Attachment*. Filter for email messages that have, or don't have, file\n"
"attachments.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:284
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Address In*. Tests for the presence of an address in your\n"
"contacts. The next field allows you to specify which address.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Address In*. Tests for the presence of an address in your\n"
"contacts. The next field allows you to specify which address.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:286
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Calendar Invite*. Filter calendar-related messages.\n"
msgstr "*Calendar Invite*. Filter calendar-related messages.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Social*. Filters messages from social networking sites.\n"
msgstr "*Social*. Filters messages from social networking sites.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:301
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Header Named*. When this option is selected, an additional text input\n"
"field appears before the comparison operator (the \"contains\"\n"
"portion). This option allows you to specify any email header. You can\n"
"specify not only the standard fields of To: or From: but also Date,\n"
"Reply-To, or other custom fields that may be included in the message\n"
"header. You can use this option to filter email messages that have\n"
"\"malformed\" headers, meaning they do not contain certain information\n"
"that is normally considered standard for an email message. Sometimes\n"
"spam, which is automatically generated, omits information such as the\n"
"Sender or Reply-To fields. Use the second text field (the field\n"
"immediately to the right of the comparison operator) to specify the\n"
"header to test for.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Header Named*. When this option is selected, an additional text input\n"
"field appears before the comparison operator (the \"contains\"\n"
"portion). This option allows you to specify any email header. You can\n"
"specify not only the standard fields of To: or From: but also Date,\n"
"Reply-To, or other custom fields that may be included in the message\n"
"header. You can use this option to filter email messages that have\n"
"\"malformed\" headers, meaning they do not contain certain information\n"
"that is normally considered standard for an email message. Sometimes\n"
"spam, which is automatically generated, omits information such as the\n"
"Sender or Reply-To fields. Use the second text field (the field\n"
"immediately to the right of the comparison operator) to specify the\n"
"header to test for.\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:302
#, no-wrap
msgid "Actions"
msgstr "Actions"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:306
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Keep in Inbox*. Saves mail to Inbox. If none of the filter rules match\n"
"an email message, this action takes place by default.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Keep in Inbox*. Saves mail to Inbox. If none of the filter rules match\n"
"an email message, this action takes place by default.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "*File into folder*. Moves the mail to a specified folder.\n"
msgstr "*File into folder*. Moves the mail to a specified folder.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:311
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Discard*. Deletes the mail message without delivering it. The message\n"
"is not in any of your folders, not even Trash.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Discard*. Deletes the mail message without delivering it. The message\n"
"is not in any of your folders, not even Trash.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:313
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Forward*. Forwards mail to the address you specify.\n"
msgstr "*Forward*. Forwards mail to the address you specify.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Mark*. Select as Read or as Flagged.\n"
msgstr "*Mark*. Select as Read or as Flagged.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Tag with*. You can tag matching messages with a selected tag.\n"
msgstr "*Tag with*. You can tag matching messages with a selected tag.\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "Multiple Actions"
msgstr "Multiple Actions"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:322
msgid ""
"You can create a filter rule made up of multiple actions. The combinations "
"of actions in your rule are interpreted as follows:"
msgstr ""
"You can create a filter rule made up of multiple actions. The combinations "
"of actions in your rule are interpreted as follows:"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:325
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Discard*. If combined with other actions, discard is ignored and the\n"
"other actions take place.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Discard*. If combined with other actions, discard is ignored and the\n"
"other actions take place.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:329
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*File into folder*. Multiple \"file into\" actions results in multiple\n"
"copies of the message being stored in different folders. If a specified\n"
"folder does not exist, the message is saved to the Inbox.\n"
msgstr ""
"*File into folder*. Multiple \"file into\" actions results in multiple\n"
"copies of the message being stored in different folders. If a specified\n"
"folder does not exist, the message is saved to the Inbox.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:332
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Tag/Mark*. These actions apply to the message returned from the nearest\n"
"preceding action.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Tag/Mark*. These actions apply to the message returned from the nearest\n"
"preceding action.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:335
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Keep in Inbox*. Multiple \"keep\" actions can be specified, but only one\n"
"copy of the message is saved to the Inbox.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Keep in Inbox*. Multiple \"keep\" actions can be specified, but only one\n"
"copy of the message is saved to the Inbox.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:337
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Forward to address*. Mail is forwarded to the address specified.\n"
msgstr "*Forward to address*. Mail is forwarded to the address specified.\n"

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:338
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filter Rule Actions"
msgstr "Filter Rule Actions"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:343
msgid ""
"A filter rule can contain one or more actions. If the email message matches "
"the specified conditions, all actions are applied in the order in which they "
"appear in the filter."
msgstr ""
"A filter rule can contain one or more actions. If the email message matches "
"the specified conditions, all actions are applied in the order in which they "
"appear in the filter."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:345
msgid "Filter rule actions can include the following:"
msgstr "Filter rule actions can include the following:"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:347
msgid "Move the message to a specific folder"
msgstr "Move the message to a specific folder"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:349
msgid "Tag or flag the message"
msgstr "Tag or flag the message"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:351
msgid "Discard the message before it reaches your Inbox"
msgstr "Discard the message before it reaches your Inbox"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:353
msgid "Forward the message to a specified email address"
msgstr "Forward the message to a specified email address"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:361
msgid ""
"The *Do not process additional filters* action should be the last action "
"within each filter rule. This prevents the application of any additional "
"filter rules to email messages that match the current rule. If it is not "
"specified, subsequent filter rules are evaluated for the mail message, even "
"if the current filter is a match. You probably do not want to have the same "
"message match more than one filter rule and undergo multiple, perhaps "
"contradictory actions."
msgstr ""
"The *Do not process additional filters* action should be the last action "
"within each filter rule. This prevents the application of any additional "
"filter rules to email messages that match the current rule. If it is not "
"specified, subsequent filter rules are evaluated for the mail message, even "
"if the current filter is a match. You probably do not want to have the same "
"message match more than one filter rule and undergo multiple, perhaps "
"contradictory actions."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filtering Using Wildcards"
msgstr "Filtering Using Wildcards"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:366
msgid ""
"Wildcards can be used in comparisons that use the \"Matches pattern\" "
"comparison operator. The two wildcard characters are * and ?"
msgstr ""
"Wildcards can be used in comparisons that use the \"Matches pattern\" "
"comparison operator. The two wildcard characters are * and ?"

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:367
#, no-wrap
msgid "Asterisk (*)"
msgstr "Asterisk (*)"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:370
msgid ""
"The asterisk * is a placeholder for \"zero or more characters of any type\"."
msgstr ""
"The asterisk * is a placeholder for \"zero or more characters of any type\"."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:372
msgid "Example subject-line search string: banana*float"
msgstr "Example subject-line search string: banana*float"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:375
msgid ""
"With Matches: Subject lines such as \" bananafloat\", \"bananas\", \"banana-"
"leaf casserole float\" but not \"super-banana-float\""
msgstr ""
"With Matches: Subject lines such as \" bananafloat\", \"bananas\", \"banana-"
"leaf casserole float\" but not \"super-banana-float\""

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:377
msgid "Example subject-line search string: w*bandanna"
msgstr "Example subject-line search string: w*bandanna"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:380
msgid ""
"With Matches: Subject lines such as \"white bandanna\" or \"whose bandanna\" "
"but not \"whose bandanna is this?\""
msgstr ""
"With Matches: Subject lines such as \"white bandanna\" or \"whose bandanna\" "
"but not \"whose bandanna is this?\""

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:381
#, no-wrap
msgid "Question mark (?)"
msgstr "Question mark (?)"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:384
msgid "The question mark is a placeholder for \"exactly one character\"."
msgstr "The question mark is a placeholder for \"exactly one character\"."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:386
msgid "Example subject-line search string: banana?boat"
msgstr "Example subject-line search string: banana?boat"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:389
msgid ""
"With Matches: Subject lines such as \" bananasboat\", \"banana-boat\", "
"\"banana!boat\", or \"banana boat\""
msgstr ""
"With Matches: Subject lines such as \" bananasboat\", \"banana-boat\", "
"\"banana!boat\", or \"banana boat\""

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:390
#, no-wrap
msgid "Escape character is Slash: \\"
msgstr "Escape character is Slash: \\"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:396
msgid ""
"There may be times that you will want to specify an exact match on a string "
"that contains characters that normally are considered wildcards. For "
"example, you might want to specify a match on a subject line where the main "
"heading is surrounded on both sides by three asterisks, such as"
msgstr ""
"There may be times that you will want to specify an exact match on a string "
"that contains characters that normally are considered wildcards. For "
"example, you might want to specify a match on a subject line where the main "
"heading is surrounded on both sides by three asterisks, such as"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:398
msgid "`\\*\\**MORE MONEY!!!**\\*` or `\\**\\*FREE GIFT***`"
msgstr "`\\*\\**MORE MONEY!!!**\\*` or `\\**\\*FREE GIFT***`"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:404
msgid ""
"To specify a wildcard as itself rather than a substitution for other "
"characters, use the backslash \\ immediately before the character. For "
"example the comparison string `\"\\\\*\\*\\\\**\\*\\\\*\\*\"` specifies a "
"subject with three asterisks before and after any string in the middle "
"(including spaces)."
msgstr ""
"To specify a wildcard as itself rather than a substitution for other "
"characters, use the backslash \\ immediately before the character. For "
"example the comparison string `\"\\\\*\\*\\\\**\\*\\\\*\\*\"` specifies a "
"subject with three asterisks before and after any string in the middle "
"(including spaces)."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:405
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing Filters"
msgstr "Viewing Filters"

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:407
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing Existing Filters"
msgstr "Viewing Existing Filters"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:410
msgid "You can view the filters that you have defined and their status."
msgstr "You can view the filters that you have defined and their status."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:414
msgid "To view information about a particular filter, double-click it."
msgstr "To view information about a particular filter, double-click it."

#. type: Title ===
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:415
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing Filter Order"
msgstr "Viewing Filter Order"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:419
msgid ""
"Active filters are applied in the order that they are listed. You can change "
"the order."
msgstr ""
"Active filters are applied in the order that they are listed. You can change "
"the order."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:423
msgid "Use the Move Up and Move Down buttons to change the order."
msgstr "Use the Move Up and Move Down buttons to change the order."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:429
msgid ""
"An email message is evaluated by each active filter unless you specify that "
"a message is treated only by the first filter that it matches. Usually, you "
"do not want other filters applied to a message once there is a match because "
"the message can undergo multiple, perhaps contradictory, actions."
msgstr ""
"An email message is evaluated by each active filter unless you specify that "
"a message is treated only by the first filter that it matches. Usually, you "
"do not want other filters applied to a message once there is a match because "
"the message can undergo multiple, perhaps contradictory, actions."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:430
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing a Filter"
msgstr "Editing a Filter"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:433
msgid "You can modify an existing filter."
msgstr "You can modify an existing filter."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:437
msgid "Select the filter that you want to change."
msgstr "Select the filter that you want to change."

#. type: Title ==
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:445
#, no-wrap
msgid "Applying a Filter"
msgstr "Applying a Filter"

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:450
msgid ""
"You can apply a filter to email messages that you have already received. "
"Using a filter is a quick way to organize email by moving messages into "
"folders."
msgstr ""
"You can apply a filter to email messages that you have already received. "
"Using a filter is a quick way to organize email by moving messages into "
"folders."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:454
msgid "Click *Run Filter*."
msgstr "Click *Run Filter*."

#. type: Plain text
#: usingmailfilters.adoc:456
msgid "Select the folders to apply the filter."
msgstr "Select the folders to apply the filter."
